theorem Topology.interior_closure_interior_closure_eq {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure (interior (closure A))) = interior (closure A) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · intro x hx
    have hsubset : closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A := by
      have : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
      exact closure_mono this
    exact (interior_mono hsubset) hx
  · intro x hx
    have hsubset : interior (closure A) ⊆
        interior (closure (interior (closure A))) := by
      have hopen : IsOpen (interior (closure A)) := isOpen_interior
      have hsub : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) :=
        subset_closure
      exact interior_maximal hopen hsub
    exact hsubset hx

theorem Topology.P2_of_isOpen {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    IsOpen A → Topology.P2 (A := A) := by
  intro hA
  dsimp [Topology.P2]
  intro x hx
  -- Since `A` is open, its interior is itself.
  have hx_int : x ∈ interior A := by
    simpa [hA.interior_eq] using hx
  -- Monotonicity of `interior` gives the required inclusion.
  have hsubset : interior A ⊆ interior (closure (interior A)) :=
    interior_mono (subset_closure : interior A ⊆ closure (interior A))
  exact hsubset hx_int

theorem Topology.P2_iff_P3_of_open {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : IsOpen A) :
    Topology.P2 (A := A) ↔ Topology.P3 (A := A) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P2, Topology.P3]
  have h_int : interior A = A := hA.interior_eq
  simpa [h_int] using
    (Iff.rfl :
      (A ⊆ interior (closure (interior A))) ↔
      (A ⊆ interior (closure (interior A))))
